---
title: "Not Just Another Course: My Second Chance at Learning"
author: Srivalli Mannem
vinternship_id: WIN25528R
---

Most students think an internship is just about adding a line to a resume. To be honest, a few weeks ago, I thought the same. But my journey with the VLED Lab at IIT Ropar changed that perspective completely.

I was selected for this internship based on my NPTEL score, and I was over the moon. But due to strict academic commitments at my college, I had to make the heartbreaking decision to withdraw. I thought I had lost the opportunity forever.

However, life and Sudarshan Iyengar sir, gave me a second chance. I was allowed to join the current cohort. That moment taught me my first lesson before I even wrote a single line of code, that is opportunities are rare, and when you get a second one, you give it everything you have.

I am currently working through the MERN stack. I have finished the modules on JavaScript and TypeScript, and I am about to dive into React, MongoDB, and Express. But listing these technologies doesn't explain how I am learning them.

In college or on YouTube, learning is often lonely. You watch a video, you get stuck, you get bored, and sometimes you give up.

Here, we use the ViBe platform. It is a proctored learning environment. It sounds strict, but it is actually comforting. It feels like someone is sitting right there with you, ensuring you don't drift away. It creates a discipline I didn't know I needed. When I am on ViBe, I am not just watching, I am learning.

The biggest surprise for me has been the support system. Usually, when you face a bug in your code, it is frustrating. You feel stuck. Here, the developer team is always there to help resolve bugs and guide us.

Then there are the Stand-up Sessions. In the beginning, I was nervous about them. Now, I realize they are my daily dose of motivation. Connecting with seniors and hearing their experiences makes the goal feel achievable. Itâ€™s not just about "Positive Vibes Only", it is about real people helping each other grow.

As I prepare to start React, I am a little nervous but mostly excited. This isn't just a checklist of topics anymore. This is a challenge.

I am grateful to my college, R.V.R. & J.C. College of Engineering, for introducing me to NPTEL, and to the entire team at IIT Ropar, VLED Lab, and Annam.ai. Thank you for the second chance. I promise to make it count.

